kubectl apply -f doesn't support all the features
like: env var
so we have to start everything from begining

Environment:
      x:           5
      firewaller:  working in village
	  
kubectl set

These commands help you make changes 
to existing application resources.	  

in kubernetes world we call programe file as manifest

kubectl set env RESOURCE/NAME KEY_1=VAL_1 ... KEY_N=VAL_N [options]
  
  
notepad day6pod.yaml
kubectl apply -f day6pod.yaml
kubectl get all --all
kubectl exec -it my6thpod -- bash
kubectl set env pod my6thpod y=6

kubectl set env -h
kubectl get pods
kubectl get pods -w
kubectl logs pods/dbpod
kubectl get events
kubectl describe pods/dbpod
